On a nice brisk Alabama winter day...low 30's, I can drive 3300 rpm for an
hour and my oil temp will stabilize and not go over 180 degrees. I have
oil temp/pressure gauges and a working thermostat.

If it's in the 40's or so, an extended drive will get me up to 210.

